<TEXT>
feliz ganz a pianist and educator in the united 
states and abroad suffered an apparent heart attack and died in 
the middle of a performance officials said wednesday he was 68 
ganz was playing the harpsicord in a twoperson recital before 
about 200 people at roosevelt universitys chicago musical college 
when he was stricken school officials said 
he was right in the middle of the concert when he slumped over 
the keyboard said earl schub dean of chicago musical college 
it was as you can imagine a very unbelievable sight and very 
shocking 
he was pronounced dead at northwestern memorial hospital at 217 
pm a hospital administrator said 
ganz was a parttime professor of keyboard and of music history 
he was born in basel switzerland and emigrated to the united 
states in 1947 after graduating from the university of basel he 
received a masters degree from chicago musical college in 1948 and 
a doctorate from northwestern university in 1960 
ganz was dean of chicago musical college from 1970 to 1981 and 
served as a parttime professor and professor emeritus after his 
retirement in 1988 
he judged musical competitions served as a lecturer and 
contributed articles to music journals 
</TEXT>
