agreement all but one of the five is married the four that are 
all have children one found out the other day his wife is pregnant 
with their fourth child 
as far as morale thats the biggest problem kevin wilde 
of sioux city iowa said of the possible loss of the pay known as 
bas basic allowance for subsistence for these men it amounts to 
an extra 180 a month about 20 percent of their total pay 
their commanding officer interjects saying that for now the air 
forces tactical air command has kept up the payments but that 
congress will have to act to keep the money flowing if the the bas 
payments are to continue throughout the us deployment 
the airmen complain a bit about the heat and the long hours 
spent hunched under the seemingly endless line of f15s needing 
maintenance 
airman adam bayes describes the days this way you go to work 
for 12 hours go home get clean go to bed wake up get clean 
whatever do your laundry if you can do that come to work work 
go home sleep its getting to be a routine 
so much so that wilde spent his day off this week sitting around 
watching his buddies work 
i didnt know what else to do he said 
during a visit to the troops last week georgia sen sam nunn 
was pulled aside by col john mcbroom commander of the first 
tactical fighter wing mcbrooms message do something to keep the 
extra money flowing to the families back home 
there are some indications congress might heed the advice of 
mcbroom and other commanders in the saudi desert 
at a white house meeting wednesday sen john glenn dohio 
suggested that congress and the administration agree on a pay and 
income tax incentive package for the troops deployed in saudi 
arabia to forestall a morale problem 
the airmen interviewed wednesday predict just such problems if 
the money is cut off as the law stands now servicemen lose the 
extra payments when they get free meals 
every serviceman here that has heard about it is in an 
uproar said jessen 
theyre telling us that for the opportunity to go and sweat 
over in saudi arabia you may pay me uncle sam 180 a month 
jessen said weve got family at home depending on that money and 
we cant afford to lose it 
