three radical leftists have agreed to plead 
guilty to a 1983 bombing at the us capitol and to setting off 
bombs at seven other sites in new york and washington 
as part of their deal with prosecutors charges against three 
codefendants are to be dropped 
laura j whitehorn linda s evans and marilyn j buck are 
scheduled to appear in us district court on friday to plead 
guilty to participating in a twoyear campaign of armed 
propaganda to set off bombs at government buildings and private 
offices according to court documents 
the bombs caused property damage but did not injure any people 
the nov 7 1983 blast at the capitol blew a hole in a wall 
outside the us senate chamber damaged five paintings and knocked 
the door to democratic leader robert byrds office off its hinges 
bombing charges against three other members of the group which 
called itself the armed resistance unit the revolutionary fighting 
group or the red guerrilla resistance would be dropped as part of 
the deal 
