brinks armored car near nyack ny in 1981 buck is serving a 
50year sentence for participating in a string of armed robberies 
including the brinks holdup in which two policemen and a guard were 
killed 
the plea agreement was revealed in court papers filed last week 
in federal court in washington the filing by us attorney jay 
stephens gave no reason for the governments decision to settle the 
case saying only it was in the interest of justice 
attorneys familiar with the case said a supreme court ruling 
about double jeopardy in may influenced the governments decision 
to drop charges gainst susan l rosenberg timothy a blunk and 
alan berkman 
both rosenberg and blunk are serving 58year sentences for 
possession of an arsenal of explosives they were arrested in 1984 
while loading more than 600 pounds of explosive material into a 
rented storage bin in cherry hill nj 
berkman a physician who is serving a 10year sentence for 
possession of explosives firearms and fake identity cards suffers 
from hodgkins disease 
a seventh defendant in the case elizabeth duke is a fugitive 
rosenberg blunk and berkman won dismissal of the charges 
against them in 1989 when us district judge harold h greene held 
that evidence used to convict them of the earlier charges was the 
basis for the bombing indictment 
but the charges were reinstated last fall when the us circuit 
court of appeals here found that the doublejeopardy rule did not 
apply to their case 
the defense renewed its double jeopardy claim in june after the 
high court ruled in a new york case that evidence used to convict a 
person of one crime could not be submitted to charge the same 
defendant with a different offense 
greene has not ruled on that motion 
according to the deal outlined in court papers whitehorn 45 
buck 43 and evans 43 agreed to plead guilty to conspiracy and 
malicious damage to the us capitol the offenses carry a maximum 
15year prison term 
whitehorn also agreed to plead guilty to a fraud charge in 
connection with the possession of false documents found in the 
baltimore apartment she shared with buck and evans the charge 
carries a maximum fiveyear sentence 
in addition to the explosion at the capitol bombs were 
detonated outside the national war college at fort mcnair here 
april 26 1983 the washington navy yard computer center on aug 
18 1983 and the washington navy yard officers club on april 20 
1984 
