10 percent of 270 billion spent on travel phone calls printing 
lights and other costs 
he said the idea is better than having acrosstheboard cuts 
due to take effect automatically under the grammrudman 
budgetbalancing law unless targets are met for reducing the 
deficit 
what this says to federal office managers is you need to 
determine within your office how to cut indirect costs 10 percent 
you can do it by having one fewer training sessions you can do it 
by taking less travel you can do it by having fewer supplies 
smith said 
budget negotiators are scheduled to resume meeting this weekend 
seeking ways to reduce the deficit by 50 billion 
using data from the office of management and budget smith said 
his staff determined the government will spend about 340 billion 
in overhead or indirect costs next year smith exempted about 70 
billion in research and development appropriations to get the 270 
billion figure he said it does not include salaries 
