navy doctors were not responsible for the 
suicide of sen john east a federal judge ruled in rejecting his 
widows 35 million wrongfuldeath claim 
priscilla east had contended that government doctors who provide 
care for members of congress did not promptly diagnose a thyroid 
disorder and that the delay led to her husbands suicide in 1986 
us district judge walter black on wednesday ruled the care the 
north carolina republican received at bethesda naval medical center 
was not perfect but did not constitute negligence 
terri steinhaus one of mrs easts lawyers called the ruling 
unfortunate but said no decision had been made on whether to 
appeal the lawyer said mrs east had no comment 
a government lawyer said the decision vindicates the doctors 
the physicians have had to live with a cloud over their careers 
for some period of time said assistant us attorney ira oring 
blacks ruling came four months after an eightweek trial he 
presided over without a jury 
east 55 a firstterm senator killed himself by running his 
car in the closed garage of his greenville nc home he left a 
note accusing his doctors of having ruined my health 
easts hyperthyroidism was discovered after a resident doctor at 
bethesda ordered a test on east in april 1985 hypothyroidism 
occurs when the thyroid gland fails to produce a hormone necessary 
to regulate the bodys metabolism 
mrs east claimed navy doctors could have diagnosed her 
husbands hypothyroidism much earlier the delay triggered a severe 
depression that led to his suicide she contended 
east had been brought to the center in 1985 after lapsing into a 
near fatal coma shortly after regaining consciousness east tried 
to kill himself by ramming a chair leg down his throat 
