<TEXT>
a man told police he helped his 
cancerstricken wife commit suicide by tying a plastic bag over her 
head to asphyxiate her fearing painkillers she had taken wouldnt 
kill her 
bertram harpers taped statement to a detective was played in a 
courtroom wednesday during a hearing to determine whether he should 
be charged in the aug 19 death of his wife virginia 
i helped my wife carry out her wishes thats all ive done 
the 72yearold california man later told reporters 
harper said once his wife lost consciousness in their motel room 
after taking about a dozen painkillers he pulled the bag over her 
head and tied it around her neck with rubber bands knotted 
together he said he waited about an hour to make sure she was 
dead then called romulus police 
the 30minute audio tape of harpers police statement was played 
during a preliminary hearing on whether sufficient evidence exists 
to try harper on charges of murder and conspiracy to commit murder 
harper described to police his wifes cancer and their earlier 
commitment to end each others suffering if necessary the couple 
chose to do that in michigan because they understood the state has 
no law against helping someone commit suicide harper said 
harper told police his wife washed down the pills with coffee 
liqueur and lay on the bed while she pulled a clear plastic bag 
over her head he said they removed the bag when she complained it 
was too hot 
harper said they tried to put the bag over her head twice more 
but she kept moving her hands and head harper said he secured the 
bag over his wifes head only after she lost consciousness 
if i hadnt placed the bag i dont know what would have 
happened harper said on the tape eventually she probably 
would perhaps come out of the sleeping pills but then shed 
have been back to square one shed have been back in pain 
