we will be ready when columbia is fixed said commander 
vance brand 
the shuttles rear compartment is a maze of pipes pumps and 
valves that feed three huge engines which push the shuttle into 
orbit once its booster rockets are spent 
we do not consider that the vehicle is safe to fly crippen 
said 
it was the second scrub in less than a week last thursday a 
day before the scheduled launch launch control found that it could 
not communicate with one of the four telescopes in columbias cargo 
bay that problem was fixed over the weekend 
the telescopes designed to study stars galaxies and other hot 
objects was supposed to have gone up in a shuttle in march 1986 
