23 to send a probe winging toward orbit around the sun the 
alignment of planets for that mission wont be right again for 13 
months 
wednesdays countdown was stopped as technicians noticed an 
alarming buildup of hydrogen while the fuel was pouring into the 
shuttle tank at the rate of 8400 gallons a minute 
the concentration of hydrogen was 10 times over the limit when 
officials called a halt they continued filling the tank trying 
without success to isolate the leak 
the problem is another in a series that began with the launch of 
the hubble space telescope in april the 15 billion telescope was 
supposed to see to the beginning of the universe instead it needs 
corrective lenses that cant be put on by astronauts until 1993 
in may the columbia leak was discovered during fueling and the 
shuttle was trundled back to its hangar for tests and a new 
connecting pipe the old one was found to be contaminated with tiny 
glass beads that made a path for leaking gas 
in june a fueling test on sister ship atlantis showed it too 
had holes and the entire threeshuttle fleet was grounded 
last month the magellan space probe went into orbit around 
venus after a 158millionmile trip that began in may 1989 the 
euphoria was dampened when engineers twice lost touch with the 
probe they said wednesday that magellan will start mapping the 
surface of venus later this month even if they dont figure out 
the communications blackouts 
