we dont have time for any attitudes he told his men all 
neighbors from around allendale sc an attitude is going to get 
people hurt when were over there were on the same team and its 
time to act like a team 
the short lecture before lunch was just another sign that things 
are getting serious for the 14 members of the 265th quartermaster 
detachment 
the water purification unit from the south carolina national 
guard trained hard this past week for deployment to the mideast 
but now the pace is even harder 
the men go about the days activities wearing gas mask packs and 
web gear to get used to the weight their forestpatterned battle 
dress fatigues have been exchanged for desert camouflage 
every early morning session of pt physical training sees 
more miles run a subject of mild grumbling among the unit where 
the average age is 35 
if saddam hussein was chasing your ass across the desert youd 
all do another five miles chided capt robert appiah the 
regular army officer preparing the men for overseas 
every night goes a little later as the 265th commander sgt 
ronnie jackson pushes his men to practice radio communications 
chemical protection and field operations 
for williams the second in command it is a question of 
survival 
called john by his men and his superiors the usually smiling 
noncommissioned officer has been less cheerful these last few days 
you realize what could happen and it makes you more serious 
said the 42yearold father of three 
williams a computer programmer is the only member of the unit 
who experienced combat he has shrapnel scars in his back to remind 
him of the ambushes and firefights in vietnam they give him an 
appreciation of training and teamwork 
i could get knocked off or ronnie could get knocked off so 
its important that everybody learn to do every job he said in 
his soft voice youve got to look at every man as the one who 
might have to take over 
the push to get ready has had its casualties for spc henry 
harris the 51yearold retired teacher it was sore knees sgt 
bill bostick 42 has a bad back sgt earnest deloach reinjured a 
hamstring all three were given light duty after being forced to 
report to sick call 
the three went reluctantly fearing they might be sent home 
there was no way i was going to go if that was the case 
said the 38yearold deloach 
after giving blood for an aids test a requirement of all troops 
facing deployment spc ulysses calhoun stretched out on a couch 
and suggested he might need a long rest someone asked if he would 
like cookies and juice 
no said calhoun i believe a big tbone and a 12pack 
will fix up my blood just right 
still for every light moment there is a reminder of the future 
after lunch the 265th joined hundreds of reservists for a general 
briefing at the posts movie theater when it ended the unit was 
asked to stay for a briefing on saudi arabia 
the reservists filed out some stopping to wish the unit luck 
the 265th quickly found itself a lonely island of olive drab in a 
sea of red chairs 
damn said spc willie badger looking around the empty 
theater all these people and were the only ones going 
