now ranges from 17500 to 35000 up from a range of 11000 to 
25000 last year 
but biden noted that the wholesale price in 1984 was 40000 to 
50000 
in addition he said while the number of cocainerelated 
emergency room cases declined slightly last year to 42145 at 
hospitals checked by the federal government those emergency rooms 
had only 10248 cocainerelated cases in 1985 
bennett asked biden if he could persuade his colleagues on 
capitol hill to continue their pattern of giving the drug war even 
more money than the administration requested itll be a hell of 
a lot harder to do it this year than it was last year or the year 
before biden said 
on wednesday bush told staff aides and reporters that after a 
year there is still too much violence too much destruction too 
many innocent victims 
he said drugs remain an international menace but declared 
that his administration would remain on the front lines until 
this scourge is licked for good 
the judiciary committee issued a report on wednesday hailing as 
a major success an increase in spending on justice department 
efforts to combat drugs to more than 38 billion this year 15 
billion over the 1989 level 
the report also pointed to increases in drug agents cocaine 
prices and criminal convictions 
among major failures though it listed cuts in the ranks of the 
border patrol and other agencies as well as relaxed controls on 
some military assaultstyle weapons tied to the drug trade 
the mixed review ranged from praise for expanded treatment 
facilities to concern that the administration may have undercounted 
by as much as two thirds the number of hardcore cocaine addicts 
which it put at 24 million 
rep john conyers dmich told a news conference that bush and 
bennett cannot deny that we are losing the drug war in our inner 
cities 
prevention and education efforts directed at the educated 
middleclass appear to be having a dramatic effect said conyers 
who chairs the house government operations committee treatment 
programs have room for clients who can afford to pay 
however the chronically addicted cannot pay when they are 
poor and unemployed as is often the case the lawmaker from 
detroit added 
new york city police commissioner lee brown told the judiciary 
committee that initial enthusiasm over the war on drugs was 
dampened by a lack of federal aid to local police 
he said new york was designated a highintensity drug area 
under the program and thus made eligible for increased funding but 
he said none of the 4 million in additional aid went directly to 
local police 
los angeles police chief daryl gates said the drug strategy 
may not be perfect but i think it is a good one he said the 
price of cocaine is up while the quality may be deteriorating as a 
result of the war against drugs 
but both officials said heroin overshadowed in recent years by 
the cocaine plague is now making a comeback on the streets of 
their cities 
brown said heroin seizures skyrocketed 80 percent in new york 
last year and are up 20 percent this year gates said the figures 
were similar in los angeles and described the phenomenon as an 
unintended consequence of the war against cocaine 
