the area code for the pentagon will change 
from 202 to 703 effective oct 1 the pentagon said thursday 
the change is in line with new telephone dialing procedures 
being implemented by campp telephone in the washington dc area 
as of oct 1 pentagon callers will be required to dial 10 
digits when making a local call outside their particular area code 
for example a caller in the pentagon which is in virginia 
will have to dial the area code and the seven digit local number to 
reach a number in the district of columbia 
long distance dialing will remain unchanged 
in addition all telephone numbers with the 694 prefix in the 
pentagon will be changed to 614 as of oct 1 the announcement said 
the 694 prefix is used in stuart va in the 703 area code 
region 
