police also fired tear gas to disperse a crowd that burned a 
shop in the sebokeng township south of johannesburg the 
governmentrun south african broadcasting co reported 
anc and government delegations met for 2 hours in pretoria for 
talks that were expected to focus on the status of anc guerrillas 
and the township fighting which has claimed more than 550 lives 
since aug 12 no statements were issued after meeting 
a radio station reported the groups would meet again tuesday 
the anc formally suspended its 29year guerrilla campaign aug 
6 the ceasefire has improved prospects for negotiations on a new 
constitution to give blacks a voice in national affairs 
