<TEXT>
federal health officials thursday mapped a 
national strategy to improve the health of all americans by the end 
of the century putting the spotlight on preventing rather than 
curing illness 
the blueprint outlines 298 health objectives everything from 
cutting the rate of infant deaths to increasing use of seat belts 
to reducing the number of smokers 
we can no longer ignore the fact that individually and as a 
nation prevention is the single most important factor in 
maintaining good health said dr louis sullivan health and 
human services secretary 
he called for a national priority for personal responsibility 
and for choices that maintain or improve the health status of our 
citizens 
such a climate would enhance the independence of our citizens 
by preventing illness or disability and this would in turn free 
up resources for those who do encounter disease or disability he 
said 
he noted that the united states spent 600 billion on health 
care in 1989 and he said that if the same course is followed the 
bill would be 15 trillion by the turn of the century 
the 671page report identifies specific health objectives 
covering a range of areas including fitness nutrition tobacco 
alcohol drugs family planning mental health occupational and 
environmental health food safety cancer heart disease aids 
infant health and sexually transmitted diseases 
sullivan said he was especially concerned about the disparity in 
health status among americans particularly for the lowincome 
minority population 
in almost every category of mortality listed minority deaths 
are greater than that of the white population he said for 
example black infants die at twice the rate of white infants 
although he stressed the importance of personal behavior 
sullivan said the nation must find ways to make health care more 
accessible to the most vulnerable among us he made no new 
proposals 
among the goals for 2000 are 
to increase to 30 percent the proportion of people who engage 
in regular moderate physical activity for at least 30 minutes a 
day up from an estimated 22 percent in 1985 
to cut from 26 percent to 20 percent the proportion of 
overweight adults 
to reduce from 29 percent to 15 percent the proportion of adult 
smokers 
to reduce pregnancies to 50 per 1000 girls under 18 from 71 
per 1000 in 1985 
to increase use of safety restraints to 85 percent of 
automobile occupants from the current 42 percent 
to cut infant mortality to 7 deaths per 1000 births 
provisional data for 1989 show a rate of 97 per 1000 
to reduce coronary heart disease deaths to 100 per 100000 
from 135 per 100000 who died from this disease in 1987 
the objectives in healthy people 2000 were developed in a 
threeyear effort led by the public health service and involved 
more than 300 voluntary and professional organizations and state 
health departments 
the blueprint builds on a similar set of goals that were set 
more than a decade ago to be achieved by this year in assessing 
progress made by the mid1980s health officials said nearly half 
of the 226 objectives had already been or would likely be reached 
on time a final evaluation wont be made until 1992 after all the 
data for the decade is compiled officials said 
however it is already apparent that a high proportion of the 25 
percent of 1990 objectives that wont be met involve poor health of 
minority populations said dr james mason assistant secretary of 
health 
we really as a nation are going to have to target those 
medical and preventive services to those people who have not 
had access to good health care mason said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP900906-0094 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
on the street his name is rocstar he runs with 
his posse fts a loosely knit crew known for graffiti and a love 
of loud dance music to police he is simply yull gary morales 19 
of queens accused murderer 
morales and seven other young men were arrested monday and 
charged with the sunday night stabbing of a utah tourist on a 
subway platform the suspects allegedly wanted cash for a night of 
drinks and dancing in manhattan instead they wound up charged 
with murder 
residents of the wellmaintained middleclass queens 
