the us military has built a sophisticated 
network of medical facilities in the saudi desert including 15 
hospitals that officials say are equipped to treat virtually any 
type of combat wound 
the hospitals include two medical ships being deployed in the 
persian gulf along with 13 facilities spread out across the 
eastern province of the desert kingdom hundreds of doctors and 
nurses who can perform anything from neurosurgery to heart surgery 
to orthopedic surgery have been flown in to care for the estimated 
60000 us troops so far deployed in operation desert shield 
washington says the american troops are here to defend saudi 
arabia in case of an attack by iraq the scope of the medical 
system clearly shows that officials want to be prepared should war 
break out 
our hospitals are just as capable if not more capable of 
doing anything we do in the states col jerome faust commander 
