resources and time millers office had no immediate comment on 
the ruling or on whether a retrial would be sought a news 
conference was scheduled for later in the day 
the court voted 52 to overturn the perjury convictions on the 
grounds that thensuperior court judge william todd told the jury 
that the alleged deliberate errors and omissions in hedgecocks 
campaign finance reports were material or substantial enough 
to support perjury charges 
the issue of whether the inaccuracies were material was a 
factual question to be decided by the jury said the supreme court 
opinion by justice joyce kennard 
the court ruled unanimously that a hearing could be held to 
consider allegations that the conspiracy conviction was also 
improper because the court bailiff purportedly made remarks that 
pressured the jurors into convicting hedgecock and supplied liquor 
for a party the night before the verdict 
todd had dismissed those allegations on the basis of written 
statements from jurors and the bailiff saying he was not 
authorized to call witnesses at a hearing 
