<TEXT>
theres something reassuring about watching a 
televised treasure hunt on the bottom of the sea 
in this type of reality tv there are no killings or threats of 
gasoline shortages no naval blockades or smiling dictators 
stroking a captive child there are just lovely dreams of gold 
thats not to say its easy finding let alone digging up 
sunken treasure a mile and a half below the waves 
the twohour treasures of a lost voyage airing sunday night 
on cables discovery channel demonstrates why 
the longlost ship ss central america had to be pinpointed 
under thousands of square miles of ocean off the south carolina 
coast 
the recovery crew then had to endure unpredictable weather 
temperamental spaceage retrieval equipment and costly legal 
fights with other searchers and a host of insurance companies over 
who actually owns the estimated 3 tons of gold nuggets assay bars 
and coins that sank with the ship in 1857 
its a battle of man against nature its also a battle of man 
against machines said barry schatz one of three project 
directors for the ohio group of investors and scientists that 
located the wreck site in june 1986 
schatz also could have said lawyer against lawyer 
it took four years and precedentsetting court rulings in a 
norfolk va federal court for his columbus america discovery 
group to establish the legal right to a treasure that could be 
worth 1 billion at auction 
while the court battle dragged on columbus americas innovative 
6ton robot retrievercamera vehicle nemo quietly plied the 
wreckage bringing up more than 2000 pieces of gold bars and coins 
through last summer 
experts believe that represents about a third of the gold that 
weighed down the steam sidewheeler central america when it 
foundered in a hurricane in september 1857 while en route from 
panama to new york 
it will take this and another summerfall salvage season at 
least for nemo to collect the mostaccessible artifacts from an 
area the size of a football field schatz said 
the ship which carried 500 passengers and freight from the 
california gold fields took three days to sink as passengers and 
crew bailed in vain four hundred twentyfive people died with 
some of the survivors telling of desperate passengers jumping 
overboard fatally weighted down with gold 
the discovery program combines documentary footage of the gold 
rush era with footage from the exciting 1986 discovery along with 
satellitedelivered views from the recovery vessel arctic 
discoverer to update the progress of current salvage efforts 
nemos cameras reveal startling images of piles and 
waterfalls of gold coins bars and other artifacts the views 
are carried by wire up to a computercrammed control room on the 
recovery vessel 
there far from the crushing pressures and dark cold of the 
wreck site scientists under the direction of geologisthistorian 
bob evans control retrieval and research 
it is increasingly common for tv cameras to accompany 
adventurers or journalists even diplomats into the heat of the 
action but in this case television actually helped make the event 
happen 
the columbus america group in what schatz said was a first 
established its right to bring up the gold by possessing the 
site through tv images rather than actually laying hands on the 
booty through manned diving 
we were able to exert a presence and take possession as if we 
were actually physically there schatz said calling the new 
legal doctrine telepresence or telepossession 
this will have very important applications for outerspace 
law he said 
the search for the ss central america begun by columbus 
america founder thomas thompson was motivated by gold but 
scientists realized the search would afford a unique opportunity to 
study the oceanbottom environment 
the shipwreck is a biological oasis schatz said it has 
attracted an incredible diversity of deep sea life 
three as yet unidentified species of life have been retrieved 
as well as a type of sponge that may prove useful in fighting 
arthritis he said 
these unexpected spinoffs are icing on the cake for an already 
spectacularly successful salvage effort 
the investors said hey lets find gold schatz said 
but theyre really proud to be part of this other activity as 
well 
</TEXT>
