<TEXT>
climb inside the 1991 pontiac firebird formula and youd swear 
it was 1967 all over again 
just like during the muscle car era theres no slinking quietly 
around the streets the throaty rumble of the 1991 firbirds v8 
engine just emanates from below even at idle 
inside are all the trappings of a traditional american sports 
car low bodyhugging cloth seats rear legroom thats miniscule 
and that big hump in the middle of the floor that indicates the car 
is reardrive as always 
sure the front and rear fascias have been restyled for the new 
model but all they succeed in doing is giving even more sporty 
flair to the car than the previous model had and a new rear 
spoiler adds to the lookatme firebird package 
some things never change horsepower image and flair were 
hallmarks of the earliest firebird they remain today 
the test car a bright speedingticketred firebird formula 
had me fighting butterflies in my stomach when i punched the 
accelerator and felt the car surge forward there was no waiting as 
the optional tunedport fuelinjected 5liter engine mated to 
fivespeed manual transmission responded capable of delivering 225 
horsepower 
suspension was stiff offering good handling but a rough ride 
over harsh bumps but i wasnt on the bumps for long this car just 
flew over them 
fuel economy was as expected a bit low at just 16 miles per 
gallon in city driving i had to get used to looking over the air 
dam on the front hood it is positioned right in front of the 
driver and with my 5foot4 stature i had to sit up straight and 
peer over the dam 
i also had to get used to the long heavy doors they took a big 
heave to shove open 
and there wasnt a lot of space in the rear hatch area 
still no one can really expect great storage space in a sports 
car besides power and handling the sound system and ambience are 
important 
in the firebird the premium sound system with graphic 
equalizer a 150 option was superb and the smallish thick 
steering wheel seemed a perfect fit the dashboard design harkened 
back to the 1960s when the top shelf of the dashboard jutted way 
in toward passengers in the 1991 firebird there was about a 
3inch overhang where the top of the dash came over and stuck out 
above the wide array of large traditional analog gauges 
typical buyers of the firebird formula are men 70 percent who 
are single said company spokesman reg harris twothirds are under 
age 35 and between 30 percent and 40 percent have college degrees 
he said the firebird in all its models the standard firebird 
firebird formula firebird trans am and firebird trans am gta 
sells particularly well on the west coast and in the carolinas and 
the southeast he added 
it is interesting to note that more than twothirds of firebird 
purchasers are firsttime newcar buyers harris said they tend to 
fall into one of two categories the first group is people who put 
great emphasis on the look of their car they want the car of 
their dreams they are not necessarily car enthusiasts but they 
do want their car to give them a certain powerful image he said 
the second group is people who like domestic cars who are 
traditional car fans harris said these people can be 
conservative in accepting new automotive technology and want a 
vehicle thats tried and true 
they certainly get it with the firebird introduced in february 
1967 the firebird has racked up sales of more than 22 million 
over the last 23 years 
the best model year was 1978 when 175607 were sold according 
to pontiac in recent years sales have hovered around 
5000060000 for 1991 the company looks for sales between 50000 
and 55000 prices range from 11985 for the standard firebird to 
more than 23400 for the topoftheline gta 
competitors include the ford mustang which has a 5liter engine 
model that starts around 12100 the eagle talon which starts 
around 13000 and the toyota supra which starts at more than 
22800 
consumer reports says 198387 firebird v8s were much worse than 
average in owner complaints of trouble and the 1988 model was 
worse than average harris said the company has made many 
improvements to bolster quality 
