producer arnold shapiro had a head start in 
shooting the cbs movie on bostons stuart murder case or so it 
would seem 
he just happened to have a camera crew in the area the night of 
the incident arriving at the scene minutes after charles stuart 
was shot and his pregnant wife carol was mortally wounded 
the crew working for shapiros cbs series rescue 911 was 
chasing the ambulance that pulled up to the bleeding couple on the 
evening of oct 23 1989 the dramatic footage of the stuarts being 
removed from their car and given emergency treatment was broadcast 
last february to a wide audience 
but the rescue 911 crew shot on videotape and the stuart 
movie became a 35mm film project the two mediums dont cut 
together effectively so everything was reenacted 
shapiros location in boston that night gave him a head start of 
a different kind however in the industry rush to film the stuart 
story the producer had a leg up on the competition 
we had all this research and all the contacts shapiro said 
everyone in hollywood wanted to do the movie but wed already 
been on it 
good night sweet wife a murder in boston scheduled for 
tuesday night stars ken olin as stuart and margaret colin as 
michelle caruso a reporter who doubted stuarts story of the 
shootings 
boston police had vigorously searched for the killer in the 
citys black community after stuart said the couple had been 
attacked by a black man a black suspect even was jailed for a 
time sparking allegations of police racism and raising ethnic 
tensions 
charles stuart who was white eventually became the prime 
suspect in the slaying of his wife as a web of evidence engulfed 
him he committed suicide in january of this year 
the racial issues this story raises are not unique to boston 
we need to explore why stuart was able to fool virtually 
everyone shapiro said a large part of this movie is trying to 
understand stuarts behavior if one police department is more 
skeptical the next time a similar crime occurs i will be 
fulfilled 
michelle caruso a crime reporter for the boston herald was one 
of the few people who doubted stuarts story from the start he 
said 
this shows you should not act in haste shapiro said the 
media and the police bought chuck stuarts story hook line and 
sinker he said a black man did it and that set off a near racial 
war the husband or the boyfriend is always a suspect in a murder 
like this why wasnt chuck because his selfinflicted wound was 
so bad he nearly died 
shapiro moved the stuart movies production site to chicago to 
