<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures about 
gypsies 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
numbers an estimated 6 million gypsies live in eastern europe 
including 3 million in romania 1 million in hungary 1 million in 
bulgaria 600000 in czechoslovakia and about 40000 in poland no 
official statistics exist 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
language romany is spoken by most unassimilated gypsies it is 
an ancient language rooted in sanskrit or early hindi and has 
evolved differently in each east european country some versions of 
romany are so divergent that hungarian gypsies for instance have 
trouble communicating with those from romania or bulgaria 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history the first gypsies arrived in europe about 900 years 
ago from northern india but mass migrations to the continent did 
not begin until the 14th century their nomadic lifestyle and 
refusal to adapt led to increasing persecution in western europe 
and migration to the eastern regions where they were allowed to 
work as itinerant craftsmen and musicians and in other nomadic 
occupations 
pressure to conform was applied systematically in the late 18th 
century when austrias queen maria theresa who controlled much of 
eastern europe issued decrees designed to assimilate gypsies 
forcibly into the serf class persecution continued culminating in 
the nazi extermination of an estimated 500000 gypsies 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

