<TEXT>
it began in a renovated elevator factory where 
customers were drawn by dishes and utensils stacked devilmaycare 
in the crates and barrels they came in 
that rustic presentation gave the first crateampbarrel store a 
formula for success showing off mundane household products with 
the flair and imagination many stores reserve for designer garments 
the notion has brought the company from that single store in 
1962 to more than 30 in six states with a new flagship showroom to 
open thursday on chicagos glitzy magnificent mile 
crateampbarrel does for its housewares what most apparel stores 
do for their clothing lines they dress up their products so that a 
customer can look at a set of tableware and envision what their 
table at home could look like just like they would with an outfit 
of clothing said george rosenbaum president of the retail 
research firm leo j shapiro amp associates in chicago 
the flagship store is another expression of crateampbarrels 
trademark showmanship offering display cases with dressers and 
chairs along chicagos ritziest retail strip 
it all began when gordon and carole segal then both 23 were 
washing the dishes one day in 1962 
mr segal wondered why he couldnt get the couples favorite 
dishware in chicago and they decided there was a gap in the local 
market 
they quit their jobs his in real estate hers in teaching 
raised 17000 and set out to fill the gap with the first 
crateampbarrel 
it was all created out of a desire to be different said mr 
segal president and owner of the store chain 
it operates under the corporate name euromarket designs inc 
based in the chicago suburb of northbrook mrs segal pulled away 
to start her own catering business and has since retired 
when they started the usual places to stock ones kitchen and 
dining room were department stores where the goods often were 
warehoused in unobtrusive places mr segal said 
it was really a dreadful part of the store he said it 
was always hidden away on the top floor 
retail analysts and experts say crateampbarrel brought a new 
strategy to the housewares business by giving as much attention to 
the overall look of the store as to the types of goods it sells 
crateampbarrel has always been considered innovative in terms of 
color and style of their housewares and especially in the way they 
display them said kimberly rawn spokeswoman for the 
chicagobased national housewares manufacturers association 
mr segal describes his company as a blend of artists and 
businessmen 
its a fine line he said we dont want to be an art 
gallery but at the same time we dont want to just look at the 
bottom line 
the privately owned company declines to release details of its 
finances or operations except to say its staff has grown from 
three to about 1000 employees 
it has reported sales of about 15 million from its catalog 
business alone and mr segal said it taps the lucrative wedding 
market with a bridal registry listing an average 18000 brides at 
any given time 
crateampbarrel stores are found in illinois california texas 
maine massachusetts minnesota and washington dc 
about 75 percent of the housewares sold in the stores are 
imported and the stores purchasers arent bound by the consumer 
preference studies many department stores rely on mr segal said 
if we dont like it if we think its ugly were not going to 
buy it he said just because bloomingdales sold 2000 of 
these lamps doesnt mean were going to rush to sell them too 
he acknowledges not having stockholders allows him more freedom 
to veer from the norm and take risks instead of relying on market 
tests 
hes not under pressure to increase business or cut corners in 
order to keep earnings up rosenbaum said so he has the luxury 
of moving slowly and trying new things 
</TEXT>
