bond department and the government reached a plea bargain in april 
under which milken pleaded guilty to six felony counts related to 
unlawful trading 
but the government didnt agree to recommend any specific 
sentence 
the newspaper story said the government hopes that evidence of 
additional crimes presented in a sentencing memo and in live 
testimony will induce judge wood to give milken a stiff sentence 
for the crimes to which he has pleaded guilty milken faces a 
maximum sentence on those charges of 28 years 
the report said the witnesses could include ivan boesky the 
convicted former stock trader 
