<TEXT>
mail bombs exploded at the madrid stock 
exchange the economy ministry and the constitutional court today 
slightly injuring six people police said a shadowy leftist group 
claimed responsibility 
in france the paris stock exchange was evacuated in midsession 
today after a bomb threat officials at the exchange said police 
conducted a 20minute search of the building then lifted the bomb 
alert and allowed employees to return 
no details were released about the paris threat which came 
shortly after the madrid blasts 
the first two explosions in madrid came at about 1130 am 
local time off the exchanges trading floor and on the 11th floor 
of the economy ministry a police spokesman said 
minutes later the third bomb exploded at the constitutional 
court on madrids western edge spanish national radio reported 
the six injured all at the stock exchange were treated for 
cuts and bruises at a hospital and later released no one was 
injured at the economy ministry or the court police and the 
national radio said 
callers claiming to represent the farleft group grapo warned 
madrid municipal police and economy ministry officials minutes 
before the blasts the police said earlier police had said the 
attacks bore the hallmark of the basque separatist group eta 
witnesses told police they saw women carrying suspiciouslooking 
packages entering the madrid buildings just before the explosions 
police said women have taken part in several grapoclaimed 
killings and bombings 
all three buildings were evacuated and police bomb squads 
searched for other bombs the stock market and ministry are located 
blocks apart on castellana boulevard madrids main northsouth 
thoroughfare 
the national radios stock market reporter juan antonio polo 
said the explosion at the exchange caused part of the ground floor 
ceiling to collapse and sent people rushing from the building 
the blast occurred near an elevator off the trading floor and 
shattered many windows polo said 
grapo a shadowy maoist organization has claimed responsibility 
for 30 killings since it surfaced in 1975 the last attack for 
which grapo claimed responsibility was june 15 when two gunmen 
shot to death an army colonel outside his house in the northern 
city of valladolid 
grapo takes its name from the spanish initials for the first of 
october antifascist revolutionary group an organization that 
began its violent attacks on that date in 1975 with the murder of 
four madrid policemen 
