<DOCNO> AP900906-0206 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
atlantic richfield co introduced its second 
lesspolluting gasoline thursday a premium unleaded it said would 
burn cleaner and cost less than any competitors 
arco chairman lodwrick m cook said the fuel also will help 
prove his contention that cleaner gasolines not fuels such as 
methanol or natural gas are the best way to meet increasingly 
tough smogcontrol laws in southern california and other areas of 
heavy air pollution 
he said arco would absorb the extra costs of making the new gas 
known as ec for emission control premium rather than passing 
them along to dealers in higher wholesale prices making the gas 
will cost a few cents more per gallon what wed like to think is 
well sell more of it making up the lower margin in increased 
market share cook said 
arco currently has about 15 percent of the market for hightest 
gas in the five western states in which it sells gas he said 
the new gasoline with an octane rating 92 will be sold only in 
southern california for the time being it replaces arcos old 
hightest gasoline the 91 octane super unleaded 
arco became the first oil company with a lowemission gasoline 
in august 1989 when it introduced ec1 a substitute for the 
leaded regular used in old cars and trucks 
since then several other companies have begun selling fuels 
reformulated to evaporate less easily and burn cleaner many of 
those gasolines like arcos ecpremium are intended for newer 
cars that run on unleaded fuel examples include shell su 2000e 
chevron supreme unleaded and exxon plus 
arco said tests it conducted with state and regional airquality 
officials showed the new fuel would reduce emissions by 86000 
pounds per day its ec1 already has reduced vehicle air pollution 
by 73 million pounds arco said 
cook said it would cost arco about four cents a gallon more to 
make the new premium arco had raised wholesale prices for the old 
premium by a couple of cents a gallon before the persian gulf 
crisis and believes it can absorb the additional cost without 
undue damage to profits he said 
the key ingredient in the gas as in ec1 is the octanebooster 
methyl tertiary butyl ether or mtbe the oxygenrich mtbe is used 
to replace higher polluting octaneenhancers such as lead benzene 
or toluene 
its produced at arcos carson calif refinery and by arcos 
chemical affiliate assuring arco a regular supply a shortage of 
mtbe coupled with instability in energy markets caused chevron 
recently to postpone the introduction of its reformulated gas in 
houston baltimore and washington chevron already had begun 
selling the fuel in southern california 
cook said arcos new gas contains 15 percent mtbe compared to 
competitors 1 percent while polluting components have been 
reduced for example it contains just 1 percent benzene compared 
to 27 percent benzene in competitors fuels he said 
arco the nations eighthlargest oil company sells gas in 
california oregon washington arizona and nevada its strategy 
has been to offer the lowest pump prices something its 
accomplished by doing away with credit cards and nearly all 
fullservice pumps 
huge reserves of alaska crude have also helped that strategy 
and came in handy in assuring crude supply when president bush 
appealed to oil companies to restrain price increases after iraqs 
invasion of kuwait 
arco froze its wholesale gas prices for two weeks longer than 
any other company the move reaped goodwill from the public and 
politicians a bonanza the company clearly hopes to augment with 
its new fuels 
that response was clear at the news conference thursday as los 
angeles mayor tom bradley and regional smogcontrol officials 
praised cook as a farsighted smogfighter 
no oil company has yet introduced a lesspolluting substitute 
for regular unleaded gasoline by far the most commonly used grade 
and also the grade in which consumers are most costconscious 
in an interview thursday cook acknowledged that such a gas 
would inevitably mean higher pump prices 
he said arco wont market such a fuel until congress finalizes 
cleanair standards nationwide and all oil companies will have to 
market the gasolines 
it will be four or five years and a 2 billion investment 
before we can get close cook said 
that investment will have to be borne by the whole industry he 
said while arco was willing to shoulder several millions of 
dollars in development costs on a fuel like ecpremium we 
cant take a 2 billion hit all by ourselves 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

