brusquely refused 
unlike wallenberg the celebrated swedish diplomat who saved 
tens of thousands of jews in budapest before he disappeared 
perlascas exploits were virtually unknown in the united states 
until very recently 
his name appeared occasionally in the italian and israeli press 
two years ago the yad vshem holocaust memorial in jerusalem 
hailed him as righteous among the nations of the world 
his story was discovered by miles lerman an executive of the 
us holocaust memorial council during a visit to budapest last 
fall 
the council is a federal agency overseeing construction of a 
privately financed 147 million holocaust museum near the national 
mall when it opens in april 1993 lerman said its exhibits will 
include the story of perlascas extraordinary acts of courage 
in this sea of darkness there were flickers of light from a 
few people lerman said there werent many who cared to step 
forward while other good people stood idly by and did nothing but 
their choices made the difference between life and death 
in the total darkness of cruelty and indifference they found 
that goodness has a power of its own and they became beacons of 
light who redeemed mankind he said 
perlasca speaks more modestly of his perilous feats 45 years 
ago when he was the hungarian representative of a romebased 
company that supplied meat to the italian army 
i always say the opportunity makes a thief perlasca said 
speaking through an interpreter my opportunity was there and i 
took it maybe those who remained silent didnt have the 
opportunity 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

