<TEXT>
oldsmobile dealers will offer a 
warranty and roadside assistance program on used cars by the end of 
the year general motors corp officials said thursday 
the program is expected to help oldsmobile dealers resell cars 
originally purchased by large fleet buyers such as rentalcar 
companies 
mercedesbenz is the only other automaker to offer a special 
usedcar warranty 
the oldsmobile program is an extension of the oldsmobile 
edge program offered on all new cars sold by the gm division 
that program included provisions for return of a new oldsmobile for 
credit toward a new one and a roadside assistance program 
oldsmobile general manager michael losh said that during the 
last year about 12 percent of new oldsmobiles bought were 
returned under the oldsmobile edge program he estimated a 1 
percent rate when he announced the program last year 
about half of the cars were returned because customers changed 
their minds about a feature of the vehicle and the other half were 
returned because of problems with the vehicle he said 
the usedcar program called value rated covers 
qualifying 198489 cars on oldsmobile dealer lots no matter what 
make with less than 50000 miles 
cars qualifying for the warranty must pass a check list similar 
to one used for every used car on an oldsmobile dealers usedcar 
lot the program should help dealers by offering shoppers 
lowerpriced cars at oldsmobile dealerships losh said 
its a way for our dealers to extend our product line he 
said 
the company also will offer a value rated plus program for 
oldsmobiles from the 1990 or 1991 model years that program is 
aimed at directly helping dealers sell cars that were owned by 
fleet purchasers said roy pikus oldsmobiles direct marketing 
manager 
a cost hasnt been fixed but pikus estimated it would be 
between 200 and 300 and probably would be passed on to the 
customer through the price of the used car 
the mercedesbenz program covers only cars made since 1980 by 
the west german company which have less than 100000 miles on them 
the mercedes program is also geared toward dealers 
mercedes spokesman ab schuman said thursday that company 
research shows that about 62 percent of the 4000 people who bought 
used cars under warranty last year were firsttime mercedes buyers 
72 percent said they would buy another mercedes and 25 percent said 
they would buy a new mercedes 
