fox broadcasting co announced thursday it 
will begin distributing its shows via cable television in markets 
where it has not been able to sign affiliates 
fox reached an agreement with denver colobased 
telecommunications inc that could allow it to reach up to 6 
million new households said jamie kellner fox broadcasting co 
president 
its the beginning of a relationship that will become our 
delivery system in areas where there are no fox affiliates he 
said 
fox is about to expand its threenight prime time programming to 
five nights in prime time and has scheduled its popular cartoon 
the simpsons against nbctvs highlyrated the cosby show 
kellner said fox had received letters from officials in cities 
including dubuque iowa requesting fox programming 
by extending our programs on a direct cable feed to 
areas that cannot support another broadcast station we can best 
satisfy the growing viewer demand for fox kellner said 
